   • Install: `pip install jsonschema`
   • Define a schema file (`annotation_schema.json`) to enforce types and required fields.
   • Example snippet of schema:

     {
       "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#",
       "type": "object",
       "properties": {
         "annotations": {
           "type": "array",
           "items": {"$ref": "#/definitions/annotation"}
         }
       },
       "definitions": {
         "annotation": {
           "type": "object",
           "required": ["id","book","chapter","verse","commentary","timestamp"],
           "properties": {
             "id": {"type": "string"},
             "book": {"type": "string"},
             "chapter": {"type": "integer","minimum": 1},
             "verse": {"type": "integer","minimum": 1},
             "tags": {"type": "array","items": {"type": "string"}},
             "cross_references": {"type": "array","items": {"type": "string"}},
